This paper deals with the problem of extracting structured information from semi-structured log datasets, which is a common issue in data management and analysis. The paper presents a tool called Datamaran that can automatically identify field and record endpoints, separate structured parts from unstructured noise, and extract structured relational datasets from log datasets at scale with high accuracy. This work involves techniques from database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), software engineering (cs.SE), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
